text.__SUMMARY__: Odostomia solidula is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.
text.Distribution:
This species occurs in the following locations:
Caribbean Sea
Cuba
Gulf of Mexico
Jamaica
Mexico
Puerto Rico
